#📊 Databricks Advanced AI Challenge – End-to-End ML Lakehouse Pipeline

**🚀 Project Overview**
This repository documents my 14-day journey through the Databricks Advanced AI Challenge, where I built a complete Machine Learning Lakehouse pipeline using PySpark, Delta Lake, and MLflow.
The goal of this project was to design an end-to-end data and ML system that starts from raw event data and produces both predictive insights and personalized recommendations.

Over 14 days, the project evolved from simple data transformations into a full pipeline covering:
Data ingestion
Feature engineering
Machine learning training
Experiment tracking
Batch inference
Recommendation systems
Performance optimization
Data versioning
System architecture design

##🏗 System Architecture
The pipeline follows the **Lakehouse Architecture**.

Raw Event Data
      │
      ▼
Bronze Layer (Delta Tables)
events_delta
      │
      ▼
Silver Layer (Feature Engineering)
user_features
      │
      ▼
Machine Learning Pipeline
Feature Vectorization
      │
      ▼
Model Training
(Logistic Regression & Random Forest)
      │
      ▼
Gold Layer
Predictions & Recommendations

Two ML systems were implemented:

**1️⃣ Purchase Prediction Model**
Predicts whether a user will make a purchase.
Algorithms used:
Logistic Regression
Random Forest
Evaluation metric:
AUC (Area Under ROC Curve)

**2️⃣ Recommendation System**
Built using ALS Collaborative Filtering.
Generates:
Top-5 product recommendations per user.

